column8: Were you able to complete your task?
column9: Did you submit an order to Scholastic Book Clubs during this visit?
column10: Did you experience any difficulties on the site today?
column11: How likely are you to recommend Scholastic Book Clubs to a friend?

column5: I was very happy about the created messages for teachers to use.  Was very easy to post onto the platform used at my school to inform parents of the book order and links to order.
The site has minor functional issues.
I miss the Scholastic of my childhood, that offered lots of less expensive options so that kids from all family income levels could participate, and offered more classics, Newbury winners, etc.
I started as a book club kid in 69/70 .  I think my first purchase was Freedom Train.  I am now buying books for my grandchildren.  :)
I like that books are listed by grade level and categories
Thank you for continuing to bring joy to children and parents alike!
I moved to a new school and new grade and needed to update my profile
Like that I can submit for all my kids at once with their own teachers.
I always loved scholastic as a child and I’m so happy to share it with my child now.
I love scholastic.  I remember my mom ordering books or visiting library to buy books. Always enjoy ordering.
Why aren’t scholastic coupons allowed on this site when purchasing books for my child’s classroom?
Thanks for working with the schools

I had an excellent experience. I loved the flyer given to us from daycare. It's cute and interactive. My son and I colored on it and discussed different books he'd like to read. I found the site easy to use and the 'Live Chat' feature was quick and responsive. Thank you!
Wasn't too excited about the selection of books
Was able to add 2 different kids and teachers. Was a little confusing at first.
We love our book orders!! Thank you for making this fun and simple for the kiddos!
Easy to use! I love how I can preview the inside of the book!
Really Miss being able to get books for $1 for my students. It's nice to give them at the beginning of the year and all the holidays/seasons.
1st time using the new system for ordering. Called Customer Service to make sure I was completing it correctly. The Customer Service Rep. was very helpful.
very nice and easy to use website, with excellent pictures !!
The site has changed so much that its not as easy to manipulate
Seems easy to navigate so far.
Easy to find books for the correct age easy payment
this place is great for my kid
The site gets easier to use all the time. I used it as a teacher in the past and now as a grandparent.
Easy to use website. I love Scholastic Book Club
Over all very easy to order.
I have always loved Scholastic and use it every year. Why did you change things this year? I loved being able to set my own date for parents to order.

I love Scholastic and the affordability for students and the rewards to help fill my classroom with books. I love the value packs but I feel like I have most of the books at this point. I think it would be helpful to have more variety for K-3 reading levels.
Always easy to access this site! No Issues!
great books always for my 2 kids different ages :)
Love  Scholastic! ever since I was a kid! I love  being able to share a love of reading with  my little ones!
Katrina made what I needed very easy - love the live chat!
Only being able to order online is ridiculous!   Only being able to order 6 times a year is ridiculous!    If I find another ordering option for my students, I will leave Scholastic.
Very easy to view and order.
Lack of Spanish books in bundles like the English ones.
I LOVE THAT YOU CAN ORDER DIRECTLY FROM THE FLYER.
Also I had to change my password and it was very easy to navigate.
Didn't buy books yet. But we will be!    Thank you!
I love looking at the books and reading the descriptions before I buy them
The site is super easy to use and I find it very user friendly.
It was easy to submit both my kids order at once!
This site has a very friendly user interface. Easy to get around and search for what I needed.
Easy to look through and order - I like the website over the flyers!
The site was very easy to use and I love that they included the teacher's recommendations and wishlist.
Website is not easy to use, even for a tech savvy millennial lol
Great Job keeping children engaged in getting their heads in the books.
The site was accessible and easy to use.
I visited the site today to introduce a new teacher to Scholastic.
Love the promotions and free books love the “peek inside” option
I only order from this website because it benefits the kids classroom.
I appreciate that the site is very user friendly.
Happy to be a new member
The website was very user friendly.
The chat was very helpful when I had a question.
I switched districts and grade levels and you made it so easy for me to switch my account over!!
I was pleasantly surprised that I can order directly from the flyer!  That is awsome!!
Thank you for making it easier for parents to find my site and order books!
The site is easy to navigate and use and has a wonderful selection at great prices.

We did it! My baby and I just placed our first order! This is so nostalgic for me as I remember I’d always order when I was a kid! Can’t wait for our books to come! Looking forward to all the reading and fun we’ll be having together! Thank you!
Doesn’t give enough info in the book descriptions
The selection of books for 3rd and 4th graders is really insufficient
Site is very easy to use. Love the feature to just type in an item number instead of having to search for it
Heather on the chat feature was extremely helpful!!  She even gave me a coupon code to use on my order!!  I love when customer service is helpful!  THANK YOU!!
A great website. Super easy to use!
Excellent website and ease of doing what I needed to do
I realized my email was spelled incorrectly and they were able to resolve the issue.
I have been teaching for about 50 years.  Enjoyed Scholastic books for both my library and for gifts to give. Thank you.
Hopefully the update worked and I will begin receiving flyers at my new school.
The bonus point technology options continue to become fewer and fewer each year.
We love books and scholastic books are always a perfect price for us!

I am very unhappy with all the changes made to the whole program this year.  I don't like the new "bonus catalog" items.  I don't like that I can't set my own due dates.  I don't like the parents HAVE to order online!  SOOOO disappointed in Scholastic!

I am very unhappy with all the changes made to the whole program this year.  I don't like the new "bonus catalog" items.  I don't like that I can't set my own due dates.  I don't like the parents HAVE to order online!  SOOOO disappointed in Scholastic!

I am very unhappy with all the changes made to the whole program this year.  I don't like the new "bonus catalog" items.  I don't like that I can't set my own due dates.  I don't like the parents HAVE to order online!  SOOOO disappointed in Scholastic!
It’s not that easy to use the web browser

I used Scholastic when I was a classroom teacher.  You offer wonderful incentives for the teachers and their classrooms.  I love that you have books reasonably priced for all age levels.  I am now purchasing books for my grandson!
The search function was extremely helpful and responsive. I was able to get great search results from parts of a title or even by looking up types of items (e.g., pens).
I loved the letter to the families that was prewritten with the link the class code and the flyer link. This makes it so easy to post to my Class Dojo messages.
I love Scholastic.   Best teachers helper ever.
Very easy to navigate. Reasonable prices.
Since I have used this site before many times it was easy.  When I first had to use it, I found it difficult.
Very intuitive and easy to add my child, find her teacher and place the order. I love the linked books from the catalog
I appreciate the dollar store. We live in an impoverished community. Scholastic helps provide the ability for me to buy books for my students .
I love to see My daughter excited about the books.
Typically I get an email when a family submits an online order. I hadn't gotten any emails at all and thought I'd better check. I do really appreciate the email updates.
Creating an account was very straight forward.  Thank you Scholastic!
Your books are really cool thank you.
I like the old order forms much better

looking for coloring books and drawings or tracing activity books
Site and links are wonderful, giving the age and grade appropriate selection made easy.
Easy to use and get around on the website  even for this 76 year old grandmother
I found books for $5.00 that the children ordered for themselves.

I am a teacher working vigilantly against the trans... LGB... indoctrination of our nation's children.  From what I understand, Scholastic is participating in this WOKE, Marxist indoctrination campaign.  Either you're participating unwittingly, or intentionally.  Regardless, the campaign is exactly what other tyrannical, authoritarian regimes created to destroy nations... Hitler,  etc.  You're a book company... read your history books.  Nevertheless, I'm scouring your site, and will monitor all book fairs for the purpose of educating parents .  I am also supporting Brave Books and redirecting all parents to its site over Scholastic... I'm determined to help stop this evil campaign against our children and families.  You should get on board with us, or be prepared to fail as a book company for children.
Scholastic always has a variety of bookes.
WOW did you ever make an easy process complicated. Sending my kids envelopes of money back home and forgetting this headache. What on earth were you thinking?

The redesign of your site is awful.  You have taken away teachers' ability to set their own due dates and made it more difficult for all to access your books and orders.  You are offering WAY fewer titles.  I have been a long-time user of this company, even during COVID, and these changes are encouraging me to look for alternatives to get books into the hands of my students.  Do better.
Will Scholastic Book Clubs be offering $1 or 10 for $10 books this school year?  I raise funds to buy my students books each year and am hopeful these will return.
Do parents order directly from the online scholastic  book club?
Emile was very helpful! But I am sad we can't set our dates thsi year.
Old website was easier to navigate.
Love this easy to use site and that it is attached to PayPal!
I like being able to enter my own due date.
hard to toggle and find my code or site and also what each club means.  Still love the idea for using it for my class and getting books for my class.

Why did you get rid of the ability to order using a teacher's code? Teachers don't have TIME to upload parents' email addresses. How can parents who don't have access to technology supposed to order? There are no envelopes or order forms on the back of the magazine. Bad move, Scholastic.
I could t find my teacher and there was no place to enter code  GJRYN
Allow credit card auto fill to populate date
Just trying to get some catalogs sent my way.
Uncertain about flyers. Can you please send 26 flyers to my Kindergarten class, please??
I wanted to be able to change the due date for families.
Hoping you will consider adding ApplePay
Books are ok. Not what I would normally buy, but I want to support the class/teacher.
When I was a kid there used to be a dollar book section now the cheapest item is 2$
I hope I get book catalogs in a timely manner so I can continue to send them home.
I should be able to order without my teacher.
I really don't like not being able to set my own due date. The changes you've made are not going over well with teachers in my building or teachers in the facebook groups I visit.
I only found 2 bilingual books for the TK - K .
The books seem SO expensive this year.  Please, I would like to see more $1 books or Book of the Week(s)!    Thank you!
I am having difficulty sorting books by price and accessing different months from which to order.

This is my first time visiting the site and I can't change the parent order by date, which is today? WTH? I am not sending out an urgent plea to order.  Last year, it took months to get our books. Scholastic is becoming a pile of steaming stuff. My faith in you is not at all restored.
I used to do a BIG September order and really pushed it with families because of the spectacular 10,000 points that used to be offered. I don't see that anymore, so I likely won't do that this year.
It is  easy to find how to add to class wish list and book suggestions. It is hard to find how to update due dates.

This site is extremely difficult to manage when looking for a teacher that you already have assigned.  It would be helpful if all they children either had their own tab or were located under your account so you can shop faster.  I could not place an order on my phone since my child teacher was not under the book club when I was signed in.  I had to wait to get to a computer.
I can figure out how to set my due date for orders. It was already preset.
Not able to change order due dates  wish it were easier to search for specific books
I would like to be able to order any book from the site and have it included in the school book order instead of having to order other books separately and have to pay shipping.
Difficulty viewing my cart while browsing without clicking on a particular item.

I no longer see a Leo flier. I see that I can look and order spanish books, but there is not a flier like in other years. My daughter is in a Dual Language Immersion program in her Elementary. I have counted on Scholastic Books as my main source of new books in Spanish. Please start this flier. I think your marketing group should be researching and reaching out to schools with DLI programs. These parents tend to be engaged in their kids education. At my school you have to select to be part of the program. This means parents selected DLI.
I couldn't find where to set the due date for orders.  The new layout looks minimal and was confusing.

I've been a Scholastic teacher for 27 years. This is the first year parents are not purchasing books. The flyers MUST HAVE A DISCOUNTED BOOK on the cover to get the parents to your website . The book "the dot" that you're offering for $2.00 on the website should have been on the cover. Also, you need to advertise there are discounted books for $5.00 or less on the flyers if they go to the website.
I would like to see a larger selection for 4th/5th grade.

I was looking for some information as whether orders are all online this year. I was guessing they were, but was looking to double check. I ended up going through trashed emails to see if I missed something.

As a parent of a 2nd grade girl, I don't want to have to answer questions about some of the gender confusing books you portray.  If children are non conforming, those books should still be available but in their own section not in the main landing page.  It is my decision what to show my child since she sat with me and wanted to see all the books.

The prices have significantly increased. They prices are like book fair amounts. This is too much for families to be able to afford each month. It is unlikely that there will be much purchase by the families I teach or myself as the teacher. This was a shock to see from Scholastic.
will be ordering at a later date, had a little trouble updating site.  but figured it out.
I wish Scholastic had class sets of a single book title that I could share with my students for a reasonable price. I cannot afford to spend $90/month to outdit my learners with a single book title.

The paper flyers have a QR code now, nothing for kids/families to manually place an order with their teacher.  0 students and families in my class have responded/placed an order so far.  I don't think this new system of all online purchases will work with my student population.  A lot of parents don't have credit/credit cards, but they could round up $5 cash to buy their kid a book.  Sadly, I think this is the end for my class and Scholastic.
Its was a little clunky on my iPhone
Wanted to get the October flyers so parents could order and have it before Halloween.
The books I entered in the "Rewards Earned" section did not save. I had to look up and re-enter them.  I am hoping they will save for when the system automatically submits the order.
Why can't I change my order date?

I am unhappy with the recent changes Scholastic has made, without notifying Book Club account members.  I do not like that we can't control our own due dates online. I am unable to find any documentation or information on your website about the changes.  Are families still able to have books sent directly to their house? It appears the prices of books has gone up as well.
Could not add money for my 2nd kid. Very frustrating. Not user friendly at all.
I am disappointed that there are not dollar books anymore. I don't even see the books from Judy that were listed as a dollar. I try and my my students a book each month.
I shared the online ordering.  I will be interested to see if parents order.  I'm not sure if there is anything else I need to do on my part after sharing the link.
frustration at trying to figure out the order due date.  There wasn't anything, except in the FAQs.
I'd like to change my due date and the site won't let me. I have always been able to do this in the past. Why did you change that option?
I don't like that you can only order online. many of my parents will not utilize this. Also, we should be able to change the date the orders are due.
I don't like that you can only order online. many of my parents will not utilize this. Also, we should be able to change the date the orders are due.
Challenging to use the city search to find teacher
Probably will not be using the site due to the new way of ordering.

I am very disappointed in the lack of affordable books offered now. Without the Book of the Week deal and the book packs that averaged out to $1 per book, it is very difficult to get books into the hands of my students. For many of my students, me purchasing books for them was the only way for them to have books of their own and now Scholastic has made it even more difficult for teachers to do this.
I could not find the proper flyer that applied to my child’s class.
15% PROMOTIONAL CODE  "APPLES" THAT'S ADVERTISED ON THE SITE DID NOT WORK .
It seems like the book selection was down from past years.
I was trying to zoom in on some of the pictures of the book pages, but the page for some books would refresh kicking me back k to the home page.
Site logged me out in the middle of my session
Zooming in on a picture preview of a book kicked me out to the main page.

I used this site on my mobile phone and I couldn’t go back, at one point I had to exit and re enter the site.  Also, it reverted to GRL and I don’t know my daughters GRL, I know her lexile.  I also suggest you allow people to search by both age and lexile level so I could possibly find books that interest an 8 yo with a lexile level of over 1,000.   You also need more high level books for young readers.

I’m just learning to do things on my phone and I was having difficulties getting into the system but I managed O.K.   I had a little trouble getting what I needed to do but I did it !!!  Your system was easy to install once I understood what I was supposed to do .  Thank You for making it easy to put in an order!!!
Im in the process of creating my flier to send to parents. I navigated to another tab to select favorites and now I can't get easily back to the flier.
Website works and could have some design and functionality improvements

It is too bad scholastic no longer has $1.00 books.  Several of my fellow teachers do a book a month program for their students.  Without affordable books, this is something they may not be able to do next year.  In my school, these are the only books some of the students will own.

Logging onto my account, I could not add money to an ewallet.  I had to google, "scholastic ewallet" for the correct screen to come up, log in, and then create the ewallet.  Not user friendly.  I love your club, but work on making tools for parents less labor intensive.  I feel I shouldn't have to search around to find where I can fund a wallet after I am already logged in.  Counter intuitive.
I scanned it but it requires my informed not the students which it would be helpful if it stated parent dob
I cannot find where to add my child's classroom code.  Neither can I find the teacher on the list.
The books have gotten so expensive.  The new due date does not help either.
The books have gotten so expensive.  The new due date does not help either.

I preferred when the fliers had an itemized list of books with prizes in the back of the flier.  With the new method, I have to go through the flier to find which books the students chose by circling them.  It is very time consuming and does not make it easy for me to enter the order.
Would love to see bookmarks as an option for purchase.
Just trying to figure out how this new plan works and how it links parents to my account

I'm quite disappointed to see the 10,000 bonus points campaign was not continued this year.  It was such a great way to to encourage kids to buy books for their reading journey and also to get more books into our classroom library.
I have two kids and I purchased two of the same books,  one book for each child, the website did not let me select a different child for each book so I had to send both books to one child only

I was not able to print the parent letter for Book Clubs. I had to send it via email to myself. I do not like that I can not set a due date. I got my club order forms and want to send them now 9/12. I think a due date of 10/11 is too far out. I don't want to inundate my parents' emails with Scholastic info. I feel like teachers have lost control over how we want to distribute and communicate about books. I work at a Title 1 school. Not everybody has online access. Some parents only have cash. Maybe everyone orders on their phone now and has a way to pay. I have always loved Scholastic Book Clubs. I'm uncomfortable with this sudden switch.

I was not able to print the parent letter for Book Clubs. I had to send it via email to myself. I do not like that I can not set a due date. I got my club order forms and want to send them now 9/12. I think a due date of 10/11 is too far out. I don't want to inundate my parents' emails with Scholastic info. I feel like teachers have lost control over how we want to distribute and communicate about books. I work at a Title 1 school. Not everybody has online access. Some parents only have cash. Maybe everyone orders on their phone now and has a way to pay. I have always loved Scholastic Book Clubs. I'm uncomfortable with this sudden switch.
I was looking for small, hard back, sensory books for a baby shower.
Ewallet if beyond frustrating to access. website is confusing on how to print/access once funds have been added.
It was difficult to enter a second child
Wish there was a bigger selection of books
I was given a class code, I couldn’t find a place to enter that
I wish I could choose a $5 book from my cart to be free instead of having to find it and add it then delete the one with the cost for coupon code “reads”
There was some books I couldn’t find on this site and had to order from shop.scholastics.com  But overall I’m happy with my purchase and my precious kids will be so happy with books.

I wasn’t able to click “continue” because I hadn’t entered my phone number. However, there was no prompt letting me know that was necessary. Eventually I figured it out but if I was more rushed, I would have quit trying and forfeited my book purchase altogether.
I had a one time code to enter and no where to enter it

I miss the old paper order forms. I feel like there are less books being offered and I have to search around to find anything I want to order. My favorite park of ordering was looking through the paper copies and getting the free books for my classroom. I would average about $40 of my own money. I doubt I will spend more then $20 this time.

I wish all scholastic books were available to order via the book club site. I could not find some books available on the usual scholastic site such as magic school bus and the entire series of diary of a Roblox pro books.
Going completely digital does not work for every family. There are multiple families that cannot access this because it is now digital and not paper flyers.

I have a class code but cannot use it to place an order. My child had an entire list ready for purchasing, but seeing as there is no physical order form or a place for me to enter my child's class code provided by the teacher I am unable to do so. Last year was much easier.
Would not allow me to use my credit card. I had to use pat pal.
Love the site, not sure about the date to order and return. Will need to order and investigate it more.
Looking for more itty Bitty Kitty books
Can we use our ewallet in the Book Club section. I have family who is adding funds to my child's account. Prior to ordering wanted to make sure, otherwise i'll let him know.
Unable to share with parents due to error on site.  I also could not find where I could change the order date to sooner.
My son's teacher isn't listed even though she has an account.

I would like to see books that are more cost friendly. Bring back the $1 books or the book bundles like 6 of the same book for $10  something cheaper in order to help get books in the hands of my students.
did not get catalogs this summer.

The teacher dashboard has changed and I had a hard time finding my classroom code to tell parents. I figured it was the same as last year and after lots of clicking and searching the site, I was able to find it.
I was unable to edit the due date for my classroom order.
I had not gotten any print copies to send home, so I wanted to see what was on here.

I'm so disappointed with how much the prices have gone up.  I'm also consistently disappointed that books seem to come and go!  You offer Because of Winn Dixie and next thing you know, its gone.  Then, you offer One and Only Ivan and then its gone but replaced with One and Only Bob and One and Only Ruby.  I buy some of these books each year for my classes and I hate that I can't rely on you to have them all the time.

I'm so disappointed with how much the prices have gone up.  I'm also consistently disappointed that books seem to come and go!  You offer Because of Winn Dixie and next thing you know, its gone.  Then, you offer One and Only Ivan and then its gone but replaced with One and Only Bob and One and Only Ruby.  I buy some of these books each year for my classes and I hate that I can't rely on you to have them all the time.
Wondering.... is this what the flyers are going to be this year? I'm missing  the 3 different ones I get each year? such as, Seasaw so on...This one flyer does not even offer many books?

I have used Scholastic Book Club for MANY years and I am dissatisfied with how late the flyers have arrived this year.  Also, I am frustrated that we are unable to change the due date for families.  I wanted to order earlier than the date given.  The prices have really gone up and I'm sure fewer families will not be able to order now.

I tried logging in this morning and it wouldn't let me.  I did try again this afternoon and was able to get in.  I was not able to change my classroom due date.  I wanted to change that since it took so long to get physical book orders (not all my parents have internet access).  I was also disappointed to see the $1 weekly book was now a $2 weekly book.  I counted on those books to gift books to my students monthly with the sponsorship of my book sponsors from a campaign I did.  I asked for $250 to cover a book a month for each month of the school year.  The price is over doubled and I feel terrible going back and asking my sponsors for more.  I feel the quality of service in Scholastic has decreased in the past few years.
Need to have flyers to send home.
Would like to see more books on neurodiversity or kids with autism, adhd, sensory issues, etc.
It is confusing that the book club is different from the general site, especially when books are not available on both and coupons and codes don't work on both.
Why is the class order date preset? I don't want that date. We use to be able to select a date ourselves.
not happy with the new ordering system.  Looks very confusing for parents.
I can’t find the where to see the e wallet funds I added to the account. I went around I. Circles trying to find it.

Way too many woke and gay options. These are little kids for goodness sake. They don't need to see options on how to be faggots and take it in the ass. Quit trying to ruin our children. Just give them good options for reading. Be what Scholastic used to be when I was a kid.
I cannot make an account. Every time I hit "register" or "create an account" the screen goes blank and I am unable to do anything.

When I first came to the site I would get confused. I usually want to use the class book club but I sometimes was confused whether I was there or not. Now that I've done it a few times I know the drill and it's pretty easy since I have the link from the teacher.
I do not like the new format of the flyers.  In previous years there has been more choices with more classics.
Site isn’t as user-friendly on iPhone
Website worked wonderfully.  Although, I am disappointed that there are no more Judy Newman $1 book specials.
The Family Order Due date needs to be editable! Why can't I select my own order due date anymore? This is a HUGE fail. Please fix immediately.
I miss the ability to offer paper orders to our families!!!
Checking the site to make sure all is ready to hand off to our class parent for management.
If i didn't have the classroom link from the teacher's email I would not have been able to find her class page. The search was not easy to use.
Cannot amend my order to add the special item for buying more than $25.
It took a few minutes to figure out how to add my child's teacher to the order. We also used Scholastic last year - so it was a little confusing.
I wish you still had the $1 books.
I wish the option for parents to order through the order form on the back of the book order was an option again. Sometimes that is easier for parents.

This is the first time Scholastic has set my class order due date. I just noticed that today, September 11th, that my class' due date is September 13th. Since when had Scholastic set the dur date? This is not enough time for me to to send the flyer home & give parents enough time to look it over.  Not a fan of this policy.    Also, the book quality has gotten less and less, but the prices are going up. This is why I rarely ordered the last few years.
it was difficult to figure out how to set up a class account vs. a personal account
the mobile site was atrocious.  ads covered most of the screen. dropped orders. slow response

I had $150 dollars donated and another $50 cash someone gave and I was only able to get 4 books for my students and not even for a full class which I will have soon. I understand prices have gone up but I can't afford to buy books for my students any more.
Co fuses if i can submit more orders bf the date

I had a teacher code from my child’s tutor at a well known tutoring center, but there was nowhere to search for the teacher with the code that was given to us. I tried to search by zip and by school and Sylvan did not show up as a school or on the list in the zip code. I had to email the teacher to get the specific link in order to place my book order and I feel like it should have been more intuitive and easy to link my order with my child’s teacher.
viewing the flyers is cumbersome. wish you could add books to the cart from the flyer
Book selection is terrible for learning to read. You should provide structured literacy options per overwhelming science of learning to read. The phonics options were shockingly limited.
I wanted to purchase “Dragons Love Tacos” but found the Spanish version was the only one available.
Just signing in and getting my school attached to my account.

Trying to figure out the new digital only format. Not a fan, but hopefully with time it'll grow on me/my team. But honestly thinking we're moving away from scholastic book clubs unfortunately due to the change
Bring back the 10,000 bonus points in September. It is motivation for me to use scholastic book clubs with my class all year.
I have always chosen the date for parents to submit their orders and found that I can no longer change the date given on the website.
good search options  prices kind of high for us but I like the formatting

Dear Scholastic,    I have very fond memories of Scholastic book orders from when I was a kid. I LOVED ordering books and my parents, although they struggled, always made sure my brother and received new books as much as possible. Now, as a parent of 3 kids, I thought I would love ordering books with them too - but the selections are just not very good. We have a generous budget and would probably spend more on books if the selection was better and actually focused on books. Instead, we generally order a minimum of books through our schools Book Trust program  and purchase better books from other sources like our local bookstore. My kids do not need more plastic junk and toys with every book - and Book Trust (thankfully) doesn't support books with toys either so that eliminates a lot of your books in each order form.  Can you please focus more on kids literature and less on junk that will only end up in the landfill? We'd definitely spend more if you did. Thanks for listening!
I prefer the old system of the flyers.  Books seem to have gotten crazy expensive.  I have used Scholastic for 33 years and for the first time, I feel that selection is limited and overpriced.
